SIMPLE: miscue
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miscue
<hw>Mis*cue"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Billiards)</fld> <def>A false stroke with a billiard cue, the cue
slipping from the ball struck without impelling it as desired.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>To make a mistake;</def>
<specif>especially</specif> <def>to fail to execute a necessary or
expected action at the proper time, such as making a play in sports, or
saying one's line in a drama.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misdate</ent>⟦br⟧
